# 📊 Vortex Tech Data Science Internship – Week 2

## Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) with Business Insights

### 📌 Project Overview

This project was completed as part of the **Vortex Tech Data Science & Analytics Internship Program 2026 (Week 2)**.

The objective of this project was to perform **Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)** on the Super Store Sales dataset to discover meaningful patterns, relationships, and trends using statistical analysis and data visualization.

---

## 📂 Dataset

* **Dataset:** Super Store Sales Dataset (Kaggle)
* **Format:** CSV
* **Domain:** Retail Sales

The dataset contains information about customer orders, shipping details, product categories, regions, and sales. Additional features were engineered from the existing data to support deeper analysis.

---

## 🎯 Objectives

* Review and clean the dataset
* Perform exploratory data analysis (EDA)
* Create additional features from date columns
* Analyze relationships between variables
* Visualize sales patterns using charts and graphs
* Generate meaningful business insights
* Summarize key findings

---

## 🛠 Technologies Used

* Python
* Google Colab
* Pandas
* NumPy
* Matplotlib
* Seaborn

---

## 📈 Exploratory Analysis Performed

* Data overview and summary statistics
* Missing value analysis
* Duplicate record check
* Feature engineering

  * Shipping Days
  * Order Month
  * Order Year
* Correlation Heatmap
* Scatter Plot (Sales vs Shipping Days)
* Monthly Sales Trend
* Sales by Category
* Sales by Region
* Sales by Customer Segment

---

## 🔍 Key Business Insights

* Sales performance varies across product categories, helping identify the strongest-performing categories.
* Regional analysis highlights differences in sales across geographical markets.
* Customer segments contribute differently to total sales, providing insights into customer purchasing behavior.
* Monthly sales trends reveal seasonal fluctuations that can support business planning.
* Feature engineering enabled additional analysis by deriving shipping duration and time-based features from the existing dataset.

---

## ▶️ How to Run

1. Clone this repository or download the project files.
2. Open the notebook in Google Colab or Jupyter Notebook.
3. Place the dataset (`super store.csv`) in the same directory as the notebook.
4. Run all notebook cells from top to bottom.

